&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-e5f9ae2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; data-id=&quot;e5f9ae2&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-widget-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-e5f9ae2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; data-id=&quot;e5f9ae2&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-widget-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;We are seeking a skilled Composite Manufacturing Technician to join our composites team in New Orleans. This role focuses on hands on production of high-quality composite components used in the wind energy, automotive, and aerospace industries. The ideal candidate has hands-on experience with a variety of composite manufacturing methods and is capable of supporting field service teams when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-74eb47b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot; data-id=&quot;74eb47b&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-widget-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manufacture high-quality composite components following established specifications and quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;Perform composite fabrication using VARTM, resin infusion, pre-preg, hand layup, and other advanced composite processes.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;Maintain a safe, clean, and organized work environment, ensuring compliance with safety and quality procedures.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;Assist in developing and refining manufacturing processes to improve efficiency and product reliability.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;Collaborate with engineering, quality, and service teams to resolve technical issues.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;Support field service operations as needed, including travel to customer or project sites.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;Conduct inspections, repairs, and adjustments on composite parts in the field or at the factory.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-7b219a8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot; data-id=&quot;7b219a8&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-widget-container&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Minimum 2 years of experience manufacturing composite components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;Strong proficiency with composite processing techniques such as VARTM, infusion, pre-preg, layups, trimming, curing, and finishing.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;Solid understanding of composite materials, structural behavior, curing reactions, and process–material interactions.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&q

&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-e5f9ae2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; data-id=&quot;e5f9ae2&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-widget-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;We are seeking an experienced and detail-oriented&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Controller&lt;/strong&gt; to manage financial, accounting, and banking activities while ensuring accuracy, compliance, and strategic alignment with our business objectives. The Financial Controller will be responsible for managing the accounting operations, preparing financial reports, developing budgets, and ensuring compliance with financial regulations. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in GAAP accounting, manufacturing accounting, inventory management, and supply chain financial oversight, with expertise in financial system management. This role requires a proactive leader who can drive financial excellence in a fast-paced, innovative environment. They will be a key member of our finance team providing trustworthy guidance and reporting.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-74eb47b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot; data-id=&quot;74eb47b&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-widget-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee day-to-day accounting operations, including accounts payable/receivable, general ledger, and bank reconciliations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparation and analysis of financial statements in compliance with Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare timely and accurate monthly, quarterly, and annual financial reports and statements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the budgeting, forecasting, and financial planning processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor financial performance and provide variance analysis and recommendations for improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with all tax, legal, and regulatory requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage internal controls and implement processes to improve financial accuracy and efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage manufacturing accounting and project processes, including cost accounting, bill of materials analysis, inventory valuation, tracking, and reconciliation to support production planning and financial reporting in a manufacturing environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide financial oversight for supply chain, including vendor cost analysis, procurement, and monitoring of supply chain financial processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits and ensure accurate and timely audit deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Payroll and 401K and benefits systems with our external partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage company credit cards&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee all insurance to ensure compliance and regulations are met, including risk assessment, policy renewals, and claims coordination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-7b219a8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot; data-id=&quot;7b219a8&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-widget-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field; CPA or CMA designation preferred&lt;/li&gt

&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-e5f9ae2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; data-id=&quot;e5f9ae2&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-widget-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-e5f9ae2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; data-id=&quot;e5f9ae2&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-widget-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;We are seeking a motivated&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Junior Project Leader Intern&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to support project coordination and execution within Quality and Manufacturing Engineering. This internship provides hands-on experience in leading and contributing to small-scale projects in a composites and wind energy environment.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;As an intern, you will work closely with cross-functional teams including Quality, Manufacturing Engineering, Operations, and Technical Leadership to gain practical exposure to project management, quality systems, and continuous improvement initiatives.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-74eb47b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot; data-id=&quot;74eb47b&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-widget-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementToProof&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and assist in coordinating quality and continuous improvement projects, including helping develop project plans, timelines, and deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in and help document cross-functional sessions (e.g., FMEA, lessons learned, process improvement discussions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track project milestones, action items, and risks, and assist with status reporting to stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Support Quality Management System (QMS) documentation updates and control&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with tracking nonconformance reports (NCRs) and corrective/preventive actions (CAPAs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to audit preparation and support internal/external audits (AS9100D / ISO 9001)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help with data collection, analysis, and reporting using Excel, SharePoint, and Power BI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Operations and Manufacturing Engineering teams on project-related activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-7b219a8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot; data-id=&quot;7b219a8&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-widget-container&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 1;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Currently pursuing (or recently completed) a degree in Engineering Management, Industrial Engineering, Project Management, or a related STEM field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Familiar with Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, PowerPoint); experience with SharePoint or Power BI is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Detail-oriented, proactive, and eager to learn in a hands-on environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li sty

&lt;div class=&quot;elementor-element elementor-element-e5f9ae2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor&quot; data-id=&quot;e5f9ae2&quot; data-element_type=&quot;widget&quot; data-widget_type=&quot;text-editor.default&quot;&gt;
